Description: Manufacturer of beneficial agricultural bacteria and fungi that unlock pathways to superior plant health and yield.
Full Description: Applied Biotech Industries (ABI) is a Wisconsin, USA based biotech company that manufactures bacteria and fungi for use in agriculture.  The company produces beneficial soil inoculants that deliver increased plant health and yields.  ABI manufactures 17 strains of beneficial bacteria and fungi that each provide a specific functions in agriculture, including increasing the availability of nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium and micronutrients in soil.  Use of ABI's microbial strains leads to increased yields and crop quality, while at the same time reducing the amount of fertilizer needed.  Other benefits the company's strain offer include increased stress tolerance (drought, heat, cold, transplant shock, salinity), soil carbon fixation, stimulation of plant hormone production, organic acid production and increased root mass - all of which lead to better plant health and larger yields.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Biotechnology, Science and Engineering

Description: AI-enhanced home services: Streamlining scheduling, dispatch, optimizing tech support, and foreseeing technical issues.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: E-CONCIERGE 2.0 is our innovative solution aimed at modernizing the home services industry. It's an intelligent virtual assistant, designed to streamline the often complex and time-consuming processes in the home service sector, beginning with the appliance repair industry. This smart bot excels at collecting a wealth of information in a user-friendly way. Through an interactive and intuitive Q&A process, E-CONCIERGE 2.0 engages with users to understand their needs, determine the nature of their service request, and schedule an appropriate service appointment. Not only does it replace manual scheduling and dispatching, but it also automates the process of adding the necessary information to the service provider's Google contacts and workflow management application, significantly reducing administrative workloads. As impressive as E-CONCIERGE 2.0 is, it's just the beginning of our vision. We're already setting our sights on the next iteration - E-CONCIERGE AI. This advanced version is envisaged to integrate AI capabilities to offer more than just streamlining scheduling and dispatching. E-CONCIERGE AI will be a game-changer in its ability to predict potential service issues before the technician arrives. Using the power of AI, it will process the collected information, anticipate the problem, and advise the technician on the necessary parts and procedures they might need. This predictive function will dramatically speed up service delivery by eliminating unnecessary guesswork. Beyond predictive troubleshooting, E-CONCIERGE AI will also offer AI-enhanced technical support, guiding technicians through complex tasks and providing real-time solutions, equipping them to solve issues more swiftly and accurately. Our mission is more than just improving efficiency; we aim to revolutionize the experience for both customers and service providers. We envision a future where home services are reliable, effective, and user-friendly, and we are eager to lead the way in this transformative journey.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Commerce and Shopping, Data and Analytics, Internet Services, Other, Sales and Marketing, Science and Engineering, Software
